Twelve people &#8211; 11 children and an adult-have sustained injuries when a minibus taxi and a truck collided at the Khan and Old Greytown Road intersection in Northdale, KwaZulu-Natal.On arrival paramedics found a minibus taxi taxi, filled with children, in the middle of an intersection, loaded school-bound pupils.&#8220;Paramedics quickly extricated the occupants from the taxi and discovered that eleven children, aged between four and seven, and one adult, had been injured.Assessment of the patients showed that the injuries sustained were the only minor,&#8221; ER24&#8217;s Russel Meiring saidThe patients were treated at the Northdale Provincial Hospital.The cause of the collision is not yet known.-TNA Reporter 